title: Fatal attack on U.S. soldiers brings war home to Georgia towns
description: William J. Rivers, Kennedy L. Sanders and Breonna A. Moffett are the first U.S. troops killed by hostile fire since the war in Gaza triggered wider violence.

title: Deadly attack on U.S. troops highlights an open-ended military mission
description: The military mission that brought U.S. troops to Iraq and Syria is largely complete, experts say. Whether and when to withdraw them is much more complicated.

title: Israeli agents disguised as doctors, patients kill 3 at West Bank hospital
description: An Israeli statement said the raid targeted militants described as “hiding” in the hospital.

title: Iranian charged with hiring Canadian hitmen to kill exiles in Maryland
description: The Justice Department accused Iranian Naji Sharifi Zindashti of recruiting two Canadians, including a Hells Angels member, as part of the “murder-for-hire” plot.

title: Ex-Pakistani leader Imran Khan gets 10-year prison sentence before elections
description: The verdict, which Khan’s Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf party says was rushed and could be overturned, came nine days before a vote it describes as rigged.

title: Tired of hostile Washington, China courts Indiana and Minnesota
description: China is rolling out the red carpet for city and state officials, in the hope it will give Beijing leverage against Washington in a sensitive election year.

title: Toyota recalls thousands of cars with air bag defects, reveals testing issues
description: It flagged air bag defects in 2003-2004 Corolla, Corolla Matrix and 2004-2005 RAV4 vehicles. It will also halt shipment of other models due to testing problems.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Blinken says Middle East situation is most dangerous ‘since at least 1973’
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken said it is an “incredibly volatile time” in the region, with recent reports of attacks in Jordan, Syria, Yemen and Lebanon.

title: Desperate and despairing, parents tap sleuth to find Kenya’s lost children
description: Thousands of Kenyan children have gone missing, but a government agency is dogged by mismanagement and police often ask for money to investigate. So a couple of friends decided to investigate cases themselves.

title: The Middle East’s arc of conflict is spiraling
description: The White House may be seeking restraint, but events on the ground are accelerating in a worrying direction.

title: John Pilger, high-profile journalist who exposed abuses, dies at 84
description: The Australian-born reporter helped expose brutality in Cambodia and East Timor. But he faced criticism for high-profile reporting errors and a left-wing slant.
